1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,900
[New members of Manito Club are here]

2
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:02,250
This is Manito Club.

3
00:00:02,660 --> 00:00:04,200
[Manitos unveiled right away]
[(Octopus) Boyoung → (Pufferfish) Taehyun]

4
00:00:02,910 --> 00:00:04,200
Isn't this my dad?

5
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:05,110
It's Hoon! Hoon!

6
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:05,110
[Manitos unveiled right away]
[(Pufferfish) Taehyun → (Seal) Kang Hoon]

7
00:00:05,110 --> 00:00:06,230
Hwang Kwanghee?

8
00:00:05,110 --> 00:00:06,230
[Manitos unveiled right away]
[(Seal) Kang Hoon → (Shrimp) Kwanghee]

9
00:00:06,230 --> 00:00:07,140
Is it Lee Sunbin?

10
00:00:06,230 --> 00:00:07,000
[Manitos unveiled right away]
[(Shrimp) Kwanghee → (Crab) Sunbin]

11
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:07,690
[Manitos unveiled right away]
[(Crab) Sunbin → (Octopus) Boyoung]

12
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:07,840
It's Boyoung.

13
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:10,540
[(Octopus) Boyoung → (Pufferfish) Taehyun
→ (Seal) Kang Hoon → (Shrimp) Kwanghee
→ (Crab) Sunbin]

14
00:00:10,540 --> 00:00:12,300
[Gift theme]

15
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:13,490
The theme of this round
of Manito gifts is "support."

16
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:13,500
[Support]

17
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,460
[Support?]

18
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:17,590
-Thank you. -Deliver your gifts of support

19
00:00:17,380 --> 00:00:19,580
[Hwang Kwanghee, I sincerely support you]

20
00:00:17,830 --> 00:00:18,960
to your Manito.

21
00:00:19,660 --> 00:00:21,180
[This is what I have in mind.]

22
00:00:21,180 --> 00:00:23,900
[An idea for the new CEO, Taehyun]

23
00:00:21,290 --> 00:00:24,120
He's the CEO of an agency after all.

24
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:26,260
[CEO Cha Taehyun]
[Customized nameplate]

25
00:00:24,170 --> 00:00:26,450
With dragons surrounding his name.

26
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,780
[It takes a week to make it.]

27
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:28,660
[Not possible, yeah?]

28
00:00:28,660 --> 00:00:29,780
[Let's make a seal then.]

29
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:31,260
[Oh! That's it!]

30
00:00:31,340 --> 00:00:33,260
[The first gift is done!]

31
00:00:32,259 --> 00:00:33,260
I'm so satisfied.

32
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,140
[Tae-eun, what's your schedule today?]

33
00:00:35,180 --> 00:00:37,500
[Cram School Schedule:
13:00-16:00 = Math
16:00-16:30 = Break
16:30-19:30 = English]

34
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:36,500
I have cram school at 1 PM

35
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:37,300
and at 4:30 PM.

36
00:00:37,530 --> 00:00:39,010
I'll send her to cram school,

37
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:41,980
[Enlist Tae-eun's help to deliver gifts]

38
00:00:39,050 --> 00:00:41,050
and she'll deliver the gifts for me.

39
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:42,980
[If you get caught,]

40
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:45,100
[pretend you don't know me.]

41
00:00:45,140 --> 00:00:47,260
[He only has eyes for one person]

42
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,260
Where is he?

43
00:00:47,340 --> 00:00:49,510
I heard he's into landscaping.

44
00:00:49,510 --> 00:00:52,900
[So he prepared a bouquet]

45
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,380
It's so pretty.

46
00:00:50,410 --> 00:00:52,990
Receiving flowers would be
a good start to the day.

47
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:54,380
[How should I deliver it?]

48
00:00:53,080 --> 00:00:54,570
I don't know what to do.

49
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:56,130
I, Hwang Kwanghee, am a veteran in chasing.

50
00:00:56,130 --> 00:00:57,670
It seems someone is here!

51
00:00:57,820 --> 00:00:59,620
[Seal! I see you!]

52
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:00,900
[Ah, he saw me?]

53
00:01:00,980 --> 00:01:02,220
[Wait, did I get caught?]

54
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:03,060
[Will he come down?]

55
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:04,660
[Gosh, what should I do?]

56
00:01:04,660 --> 00:01:05,940
[Meanwhile, in the same area]

57
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:05,850
-Tae-eun. -Yeah?

58
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:07,420
[Run away right after giving it to him?]

59
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:08,620
[Here you go!]

60
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:09,820
[Here you go!]

61
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,460
[Receiving a gift right before his eyes]

62
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:13,640
What's going on? Wait.

63
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:16,860
[Hurry!]

64
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:17,380
[Hurry up!]

65
00:01:17,420 --> 00:01:18,180
[Who is it?]

66
00:01:18,180 --> 00:01:18,820
[Get in the car quickly!]

67
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:20,620
[Hurry up!]

68
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:22,260
[Who is it?]

69
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:23,660
Dad!

70
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:23,660
[The father-daughter's gift-giving plan succeeds]

71
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,950
Dad, call me at 7:30 PM. I want the 30,000 won.

72
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:27,780
[Tae-eun's contribution continues!]

73
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:27,780
Wait, who was that?

74
00:01:28,020 --> 00:01:32,259
[Plans an early birthday party for Boyoung]

75
00:01:28,110 --> 00:01:31,880
It's not a bad idea
to celebrate her birthday in advance.

76
00:01:32,570 --> 00:01:35,140
My little princess, wait and see.

77
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:35,350
[Approaching her to give the questionnaire
to prepare for the party]

78
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,000
[Swoosh]

79
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,170
They won't come now, right?

80
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:39,259
[Knock, knock]

81
00:01:39,259 --> 00:01:39,860
[Knock, knock]

82
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:41,820
[Ah, they left something and fled!]

83
00:01:41,820 --> 00:01:42,900
[Lee Sunbin]
[Sunbin hides in her hideout]

84
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:44,860
[Uh!]
[Sunbin hides in her hideout]

85
00:01:43,950 --> 00:01:44,630
Who is it?

86
00:01:44,860 --> 00:01:46,259
[I didn't even catch a glimpse of their back!]

87
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:49,420
[Ha... This is driving me crazy.]

88
00:01:49,420 --> 00:01:50,350
[Lee Sunbin]

89
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:53,300
[Lee Sunbin]
[Park Boyoung: They're that fast?]

90
00:01:54,020 --> 00:01:58,660
[They ran away so quickly?]

91
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,900
[Lee Sunbin]

92
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:04,420
[Swoosh]

93
00:02:04,820 --> 00:02:09,500
[Boyoung starts searching the rooms]

94
00:02:10,660 --> 00:02:12,820
[(Whispers) Oh no, Boyoung is coming!]

95
00:02:13,060 --> 00:02:14,260
[No, because...]

96
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:15,390
But...

97
00:02:16,180 --> 00:02:18,860
[Park Boyoung: They knocked and left...]

98
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,500
[There's no way they already
got all the way there.]

99
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:33,640
She's out now...

100
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,740
[(Swoosh)]

101
00:02:35,740 --> 00:02:37,420
[??: It's me. It's me.]

102
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:39,660
Hurry. Hurry.

103
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:41,620
[Fortunately, it's just the filming crew
who came looking for Sunbin]

104
00:02:40,390 --> 00:02:41,280
Hurry up.

105
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:45,060
[Luckily (?) she's searching rooms
on the opposite side]

106
00:02:45,060 --> 00:02:52,660
[Lee Sunbin]
[Boyoung's room] [Park Boyoung]

107
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:54,100
[No one's here...]

108
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:58,020
[Returns to her room after failing to catch Crab]

109
00:02:57,360 --> 00:03:00,670
I had a feeling Crab would do this.

110
00:02:58,540 --> 00:03:00,660
[Darn it]

111
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:07,180
[What a close call]

112
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:11,060
[I must run away ASAP]

113
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:14,220
[Cautious]

114
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:16,420
[(Whispers) I'm leaving.]

115
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:20,900
[Sacrificing her feet and fleeing without shoes]

116
00:03:21,260 --> 00:03:24,060
[Lee Sunbin: Where should I run to? For now.]

117
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:28,140
[I'm working harder at this than at my job.]

118
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:32,540
[Collapses]

119
00:03:32,540 --> 00:03:35,340
[Ha... I'm doing so much for this...]

120
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:38,620
[This is from Crab.]

121
00:03:38,940 --> 00:03:40,460
[Eh?]

122
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:43,300
[A message on the photo]

123
00:03:40,850 --> 00:03:41,900
I'm Crab.

124
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:43,420
My dear lovely actress.

125
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:48,540
[Although I'm clumsy, here is my sincerity.]

126
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:54,420
[I'll give my all for you today.]

127
00:03:54,670 --> 00:03:57,170
He's my friend who's helping me today.

128
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:59,100
[Hiding her identity
with the help of an acquaintance]

129
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:59,310
I called him in a hurry.

130
00:03:59,390 --> 00:04:01,550
Hold this with your hand so only this is captured.

131
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:03,740
[Prepares a four-cut photo as support]

132
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:02,640
I'll press this for you.

133
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:03,440
That's right.

134
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,950
This is such a middle-aged man's pose.

135
00:04:05,860 --> 00:04:07,220
[Anyone would assume it's a man.]

136
00:04:07,460 --> 00:04:08,780
[It has to be a man.]

137
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:11,980
[In accord with Sunbin's plan,
she mistakenly assumes it's a man]

138
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,630
It has to be a man.

139
00:04:12,180 --> 00:04:14,740
[Who could it be?]

140
00:04:17,459 --> 00:04:20,060
[Boyoung suddenly picks up her phone]

141
00:04:23,260 --> 00:04:25,460
[Ahaha!]
[(Taken aback)]

142
00:04:26,180 --> 00:04:27,900
[Should I pretend I didn't see it?]

143
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:29,340
[There's a QR code.]

144
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:31,980
[Sunbin overlooked one thing]

145
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,659
[QR code]

146
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:37,140
[Scanning this QR code...]

147
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:40,460
[She can see the video
of the phototaking process]

148
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:43,620
[Dopamine spiking]

149
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:46,540
[Park Boyoung: I saw a glimpse of his face,
so I closed the video.]

150
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:49,380
[Wow, I really want to see who it is.]

151
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,740
[Fighting her curiosity]

152
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:54,420
[That's it for now]

153
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:54,600
Got it.

154
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,060
[Enough deduction for now; let's eat first]

155
00:04:55,340 --> 00:04:56,100
Let's eat.

156
00:04:58,220 --> 00:05:00,620
[Crew: You didn't see him, did you?]

157
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:02,540
[I only know it's a man.]

158
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:04,330
His face showed a bit like this.

159
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:06,180
[I'll let him off this time]
[Guesses that the man in the photo is Crab]

160
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:08,290
I'll let him off this time.

161
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:16,580
[Here is Octopus' feedback]

162
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:12,440
You seem like a unique person.

163
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,570
It's my first time receiving such a thoughtful

164
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:16,540
yet random gift.

165
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,750
It's been a while since someone has

166
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:21,940
[She felt her thoughtfulness
from the questionnaire]

167
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:21,770
put in this much effort to get to know me.

168
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:24,420
[So I'm very happy right now.]

169
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:27,700
[That's right! It's me, Boyoung!]

170
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:29,300
[I think my intention came across.]

171
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:31,660
[Aw! Even her words are sweet.]

172
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:34,140
[Kang Hoon: I have to give my gift too.]

173
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,900
I'll get someone to do it for me too.

174
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,100
[Ask a citizen for help!]

175
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:36,890
Let's go.

176
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,340
[Wears the paper bag again]

177
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:41,900
[But I was so obvious. I should have done that.]

178
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:45,000
Won't he think that I'm running away now?

179
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:44,980
[Full of worries]

180
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:47,780
[Wait. Let me think a bit more.]

181
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:50,620
[Citizen 1] [Citizen 2]
[I have to ask for someone's help]

182
00:05:51,940 --> 00:05:58,020
[How an introvert asks for help: stares quietly]

183
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:02,860
[Ah, how should I do this?]

184
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:06,620
[Is anyone passing by...]

185
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:09,620
[(Whispers) Can you come over for a while?]

186
00:06:09,740 --> 00:06:12,580
[Citizen: Can I come down?]
[Yes, please come down.]

187
00:06:12,370 --> 00:06:13,170
Just a moment.

188
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:14,740
[I did it! Hehe]

189
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,570
Really? What are you doing?

190
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:18,180
[The citizen invited (?) while watching from afar]

191
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:18,180
I'm shooting a variety show.

192
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:21,740
[Hwang Kwanghee is on the 2nd floor there.]
[Gasp!]

193
00:06:21,810 --> 00:06:25,140
A full-body fursuit of King Kong.

194
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:25,100
[Hwang Kwanghee's making a call on the 2nd floor]

195
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:28,140
[Kang Hoon: Deliver this over.]

196
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:30,980
[Kang Hoon: Then say, "I'm rooting for you."]

197
00:06:29,650 --> 00:06:31,230
-Me? -Yes, please help me out.

198
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:33,090
Don't mention me. Say I'm a woman.

199
00:06:33,820 --> 00:06:36,180
[The citizen is on the move]

200
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,130
Don't be nervous.

201
00:06:36,409 --> 00:06:37,720
In Seoul?

202
00:06:36,659 --> 00:06:40,659
[Kwanghee is preparing his Manito gift]

203
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,580
Can you connect me to them?

204
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,170
In Seoul...

205
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:44,260
[The brave citizen who goes to him
without hesitation]

206
00:06:46,130 --> 00:06:47,950
I'll do it by text.

207
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:50,780
[Zero alertness]

208
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:50,400
If it's possible, send me one too. Thank you.

209
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,240
A female...

210
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:55,600
-Who are you? -Sorry?

211
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:58,150
-Have a good day. -Thank you. Who are you?

212
00:06:56,659 --> 00:06:58,780
[He takes the mysterious bouquet]

213
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:01,000
[There was a woman...]

214
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,100
Don't lie! I know it's not a woman!

215
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:05,220
-It's a woman. -I'll take a photo with you.

216
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:06,150
-With me? -Yes.

217
00:07:06,770 --> 00:07:08,450
My fan service is extraordinary.

218
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:09,460
[Forced fan service]

219
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:09,440
Wow.

220
00:07:09,740 --> 00:07:11,070
[A man asked you for help, right?]

221
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,630
-No, no. -It's Mingyu, right?

222
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,720
-Wow, I'm a fan of Mingyu. -Really?

223
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:16,820
[Looks like I guessed right.]

224
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:18,350
1, 2, 3.

225
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,060
Thank you.

226
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,780
[Leaving right after completing the mission]

227
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,010
What's with these flowers?

228
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:25,540
[Hwang Kwanghee: How'd he know I like them?]

229
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:29,260
[It's not easy for hydrangeas to bloom.]

230
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:33,300
[Hwang Kwanghee: He's great at getting gifts.
Did he run around with this?]

231
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:36,060
[Thank you, Seal.]

232
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:38,340
[Wow! His handwriting is so nice!]

233
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:40,950
"Kwanghee, I've seen you a lot on variety shows.

234
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:43,360
Thanks to you, I have great entertainment to

235
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,380
eat meals with and watch during my leisure time."
Wow.

236
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:48,780
I feel so supported.

237
00:07:48,780 --> 00:07:53,020
"You brought laughter into my life
when I felt lonely.

238
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:55,620
I'll always support you." Wow.

239
00:07:56,180 --> 00:07:58,700
[Ah, so this is support.]

240
00:07:58,930 --> 00:08:00,440
It's the same for me.

241
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:03,980
[Hwang Kwanghee: You know the meme
of Sunbin and Siwan (in "Boyhood")?]

242
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,220
It was very funny.

243
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:07,580
[The letter he received reminds him of his Manito]

244
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:07,030
I was so happy when I watched it.

245
00:08:08,140 --> 00:08:10,940
[Sunbin also brought laughter into my life.]

246
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:13,220
[I should write my letter right now.]

247
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:15,940
[To Sunbin]

248
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:22,820
[I did my best to prepare the support gifts,
but I'm sorry that I'm not the best at it.]

249
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:26,140
[Watching your great acting in
"Work Later, Drink Now" and "Boyhood"
really helped relieve stress.
I look forward to meeting you sometime!]

250
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,260
I'll keep cheering for you.

251
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:29,300
[My spirits are high
now that I've received a gift.]

252
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,120
[Kang Hoon's support gift:
flowers and a sincere letter]

253
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,820
This is the beauty of gifts.

254
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:34,940
[To Kwanghee: I've seen you a lot on
variety shows. I know how tough it is to be
on them, and how much effort you must've
put into it. I can relate a little to how tough
it is. Just a little. Thank you for always being
positive and bringing laughter.]

255
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:34,880
Really. It instantly lifted my mood.

256
00:08:35,299 --> 00:08:38,780
[Boyoung's agency]

257
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:37,100
Hello, I'm back.

258
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,799
I'm in big trouble.

259
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:41,059
[Park Boyoung: Only my Pufferfish...]

260
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:43,700
[Only Pufferfish hasn't received his gift yet!]

261
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:47,220
[Let's quickly make a nameplate!]

262
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:47,120
Can I turn this into a triangular prism?

263
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:50,260
[I just need to connect them and paste them.]

264
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:52,660
[I only get one try!]

265
00:08:53,060 --> 00:08:54,620
[There's no turning back.]

266
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:57,900
[(Careful)]

267
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:57,890
It's like pasting phone screen shields.

268
00:08:58,030 --> 00:09:00,770
It really sticks well.

269
00:08:58,260 --> 00:09:00,460
[After folding it into a triangular prism...]

270
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:04,220
[The completed nameplate frame looks decent]

271
00:09:02,050 --> 00:09:04,460
The front looks the best.

272
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:06,260
[CEO]
[The wording is done by printing and cutting]

273
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:08,190
Now, how should I cut it and paste it?

274
00:09:06,260 --> 00:09:08,700
[Cha] [Tae]

275
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:12,380
[Focused]

276
00:09:09,570 --> 00:09:10,880
Oh! Oh my!

277
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:14,180
[Have some coffee. It'll be a while.]

278
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:16,860
[Confident]

279
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:19,680
I'm almost done now.

280
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:22,260
[Non-stop cutting as she thinks about
how much Dad will love this]

281
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,240
