2521
01:25:23,590 --> 01:25:27,040
[Park Boyoung: If the last person isn't a girl,]

2522
01:25:27,540 --> 01:25:30,220
[I probably know who Sunbin is!]

2523
01:25:30,550 --> 01:25:31,280
-Tell us.
-No.

2524
01:25:30,810 --> 01:25:32,430
[Wait… really?]

2525
01:25:31,280 --> 01:25:33,540
-Wait… really?
-That nickname...

2526
01:25:33,170 --> 01:25:35,570
[Arrow aiming at Crab]

2527
01:25:33,540 --> 01:25:34,750
I probably know which one she is.

2528
01:25:34,750 --> 01:25:35,710
What do you think I am?

2529
01:25:35,710 --> 01:25:37,870
[It's that postscript tone!]

2530
01:25:38,100 --> 01:25:39,560
[Hwang Kwanghee: Can friends
recognize each other?]

2531
01:25:39,360 --> 01:25:40,850
I know her very well.

2532
01:25:39,830 --> 01:25:42,580
[But...]

2533
01:25:42,710 --> 01:25:44,840
[Sweating profusely, better to talk less]

2534
01:25:45,830 --> 01:25:46,590
Yes, I don't dare to talk either.

2535
01:25:46,300 --> 01:25:47,630
[I'm going to shut my mouth today]

2536
01:25:46,590 --> 01:25:48,510
-I'm going to shut my mouth today.
-Stay quiet.

2537
01:25:48,510 --> 01:25:50,400
-Honestly...
-We need to stay sharp.

2538
01:25:50,370 --> 01:25:51,200
[Hwang Kwanghee: Did you
sleep well last night?]

2539
01:25:51,340 --> 01:25:52,850
[Hwang Kwanghee:
Weren't you too curious to sleep?]

2540
01:25:52,180 --> 01:25:52,850
-I didn't sleep well.
-I didn't sleep at all.

2541
01:25:52,850 --> 01:25:53,430
Same here.

2542
01:25:53,170 --> 01:25:56,550
[Park Boyoung: Yesterday, my Manito]

2543
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:56,770
I couldn't sleep at all.

2544
01:25:56,770 --> 01:25:59,450
[dropped a huge final blow
on me at the very end]

2545
01:25:59,670 --> 01:26:01,470
[What is it? Now I'm really curious]

2546
01:26:01,630 --> 01:26:03,270
[What does “final blow” mean?
Is it a good thing?]

2547
01:26:03,400 --> 01:26:04,930
[It is!]

2548
01:26:04,220 --> 01:26:04,740
Really?

2549
01:26:05,050 --> 01:26:06,340
[I'm seriously so curious!]

2550
01:26:06,460 --> 01:26:06,530
Really.

2551
01:26:06,470 --> 01:26:07,890
[I really like it too!]

2552
01:26:08,050 --> 01:26:09,740
[Really? Yes, I really like it too!]

2553
01:26:09,890 --> 01:26:11,270
[What a relief]

2554
01:26:11,400 --> 01:26:13,430
[Lee Sunbin: I think that
person is really amazing]

2555
01:26:13,580 --> 01:26:15,370
[Why?]

2556
01:26:15,500 --> 01:26:17,630
I'll tell you once everyone's here.

2557
01:26:15,690 --> 01:26:17,800
[Details cannot be disclosed]

2558
01:26:17,630 --> 01:26:18,990
I mean, my Manito…

2559
01:26:17,950 --> 01:26:21,400
[Where did Dad go?] [My Manito might be
the one who hasn't arrived yet…]

2560
01:26:22,300 --> 01:26:24,460
[The “elder” Boyoung has been
waiting for makes an entrance]

2561
01:26:24,710 --> 01:26:26,550
[Oh, our soldier uncle…]

2562
01:26:27,100 --> 01:26:32,530
[Oh wow, my Soochan… in 2–3 years,
he'll have to enlist too…]

2563
01:26:33,040 --> 01:26:34,370
I can really relate.

2564
01:26:34,360 --> 01:26:37,310
[The real “uncle” worried
about the soldier uncle]

2565
01:26:34,370 --> 01:26:37,180
He must be freezing. That's so tough.

2566
01:26:38,230 --> 01:26:42,040
Oh my, it's so cold outside.

2567
01:26:42,040 --> 01:26:44,050
It's much warmer in here.

2568
01:26:44,050 --> 01:26:45,810
-Bro.
-Bro, you're here.

2569
01:26:44,230 --> 01:26:45,500
[Bro!]

2570
01:26:45,700 --> 01:26:47,200
[Getting into character; Bro?]

2571
01:26:47,250 --> 01:26:49,130
Who is this?

2572
01:26:47,480 --> 01:26:51,010
[The last to arrive: Pufferfish]

2573
01:26:49,130 --> 01:26:50,950
Who is this? Oh—it's Kwanghee.

2574
01:26:50,950 --> 01:26:52,270
-Oh my.
-What's going on?

2575
01:26:51,960 --> 01:26:53,120
[Pretending to be shocked]

2576
01:26:52,270 --> 01:26:54,790
-What is this supposed to be?
-What's going on?

2577
01:26:53,770 --> 01:26:55,480
[A waste of talent on full display]

2578
01:26:54,790 --> 01:26:55,630
What is going on?

2579
01:26:55,580 --> 01:26:57,360
[Stunned]

2580
01:26:55,630 --> 01:26:56,310
What is going on?

2581
01:26:56,310 --> 01:26:57,370
What's happening?

2582
01:26:57,670 --> 01:26:59,440
[Aren't these all my family?]

2583
01:26:59,210 --> 01:27:01,120
-You've all worked together before, right?
-What's going on?

2584
01:27:01,120 --> 01:27:04,400
-Right?
-How did everyone end up here together?

2585
01:27:01,960 --> 01:27:04,240
[Wow, hahaha]

2586
01:27:04,400 --> 01:27:05,470
All worked together before.

2587
01:27:05,040 --> 01:27:08,130
[Episode 3: All Manito members are present]

2588
01:27:05,470 --> 01:27:07,230
-Dad.
-Wait.

2589
01:27:07,230 --> 01:27:08,260
This is my dad.

2590
01:27:08,260 --> 01:27:09,650
How did everyone end up here together?

2591
01:27:09,650 --> 01:27:11,340
Seriously, that startled me.

2592
01:27:11,340 --> 01:27:12,650
Dad, sit in the middle.

2593
01:27:12,650 --> 01:27:13,470
What is going on?

2594
01:27:13,250 --> 01:27:15,120
[Hwang Kwanghee: So, is everyone here now?]

2595
01:27:14,680 --> 01:27:16,670
Bro.

2596
01:27:16,430 --> 01:27:19,380
[Seeing familiar faces, a smile naturally appears]

2597
01:27:16,670 --> 01:27:19,330
Honestly, was this arranged on purpose?

2598
01:27:19,520 --> 01:27:22,050
[Cha Taehyun: What is going on? I had no idea]

2599
01:27:21,920 --> 01:27:24,320
Oh, I had no idea.

2600
01:27:25,130 --> 01:27:26,740
[Why are you suddenly lifting your foot?]

2601
01:27:27,150 --> 01:27:28,530
Nothing.

2602
01:27:27,420 --> 01:27:30,360
[(Dad, what are you doing?)]

2603
01:27:32,330 --> 01:27:36,420
[Planning to show the shoes received
and guess the Manito by their reaction]

2604
01:27:32,660 --> 01:27:34,840
-The older one.
-So it was Taehyun.

2605
01:27:34,840 --> 01:27:37,150
-What?
-From the tone of the Feedback.

2606
01:27:37,030 --> 01:27:40,860
[Lee Sunbin: One of them sounded middle-aged]

2607
01:27:41,800 --> 01:27:43,510
So it was Taehyun.

2608
01:27:43,470 --> 01:27:45,720
[Park Boyoung: From the tone of the Feedback]

2609
01:27:43,510 --> 01:27:45,790
-What?
-From the tone of the Feedback...

2610
01:27:45,790 --> 01:27:49,130
-It sounded like someone older.
-Who? No way.

2611
01:27:45,850 --> 01:27:48,970
[Who? No Way]
[Park Boyoung: It sounded like someone older…]

2612
01:27:49,140 --> 01:27:51,860
[You're the one who sent the medal, right?]

2613
01:27:51,900 --> 01:27:53,140
Not a medal?

2614
01:27:52,040 --> 01:27:54,560
[Nameplate! Huh…]

2615
01:27:53,140 --> 01:27:55,350
-Nameplate.
-Nameplate, right, nameplate.

2616
01:27:55,350 --> 01:27:56,610
-Nameplate?
-Nameplate, right, nameplate.

2617
01:27:55,520 --> 01:27:57,850
[Pretending]

2618
01:27:56,610 --> 01:27:57,860
A nameplate?

2619
01:27:57,860 --> 01:27:59,830
The one who sent the nameplate...

2620
01:27:58,830 --> 01:28:01,340
[Kang Hoon: even called
senior Yoon Kyungho “Kyungho”?]

2621
01:28:01,860 --> 01:28:03,300
[Oh? That kind of thing happened?]

2622
01:28:03,890 --> 01:28:06,240
[Father and daughter trying to laugh it off]

2623
01:28:04,690 --> 01:28:06,890
They just called him Kyungho directly.

2624
01:28:07,060 --> 01:28:09,780
[Cha Taehyun: I didn't expect it
to be this cold today]

2625
01:28:10,350 --> 01:28:12,850
[These shoes are basically slippers]

2626
01:28:12,010 --> 01:28:13,600
Wearing these, it's freezing.

2627
01:28:13,210 --> 01:28:16,250
[Uneasy eyes]

2628
01:28:13,600 --> 01:28:14,810
Yeah, they're running shoes.

2629
01:28:14,810 --> 01:28:16,450
They're full of ventilation holes.

2630
01:28:16,450 --> 01:28:17,710
What is going on?

2631
01:28:16,560 --> 01:28:21,360
[Will they be able to make it to Ulsan safely?]

2632
01:28:18,540 --> 01:28:19,970
What is going on?

2633
01:28:22,790 --> 01:28:26,350
[The Manito team gathering officially begins]

2634
01:28:23,020 --> 01:28:24,690
What is this situation?

2635
01:28:24,690 --> 01:28:25,570
You're my Manito, right?

2636
01:28:25,570 --> 01:28:26,540
Maybe.

2637
01:28:26,540 --> 01:28:28,230
So it turns out to be someone very thoughtful.

2638
01:28:26,820 --> 01:28:29,980
[Time to show off our Manitos]

2639
01:28:28,230 --> 01:28:30,030
I'm so happy right now.

2640
01:28:30,160 --> 01:28:31,280
[That person should be a writer]

2641
01:28:31,480 --> 01:28:32,350
[Snicker, snicker]

2642
01:28:31,620 --> 01:28:32,570
The writing is really good.

2643
01:28:32,570 --> 01:28:34,330
[I… feel like I didn't
get any support at all]

2644
01:28:34,080 --> 01:28:35,860
-Really?
-That's too much.

2645
01:28:34,460 --> 01:28:35,750
[Shocked]

2646
01:28:35,860 --> 01:28:37,410
Everything I got was useless.

2647
01:28:35,950 --> 01:28:37,400
[All of it was useless…]

2648
01:28:37,410 --> 01:28:39,480
If that's the case, bro,
don't accept gifts for the rest of your life.

2649
01:28:38,040 --> 01:28:39,520
[Flustered, flustered]

2650
01:28:39,740 --> 01:28:41,150
[Did he already throw it away?]

2651
01:28:40,580 --> 01:28:41,330
I left it somewhere else.

2652
01:28:41,330 --> 01:28:43,530
[I think we need some time for apologies]

2653
01:28:43,640 --> 01:28:47,010
[Inside the train,
the damage keeps piling up]

2654
01:28:43,660 --> 01:28:44,430
I'm really hurt.

2655
01:28:44,430 --> 01:28:45,880
From now on, don't even appear
in anything called “Gifts.”

2656
01:28:45,880 --> 01:28:47,100
Lee Kang Hoon, say something too.

2657
01:28:47,100 --> 01:28:48,030
[My name isn't Lee Kang Hoon]

2658
01:28:48,220 --> 01:28:50,200
[Everything I received was useless]

2659
01:28:50,300 --> 01:28:51,780
Not here.

2660
01:28:50,530 --> 01:28:51,790
[(My Manito) isn't here]

2661
01:28:51,780 --> 01:28:53,910
Who did I even meet yesterday?

2662
01:28:51,950 --> 01:28:55,230
[The warm and thoughtful Manito has disappeared]

2663
01:28:53,910 --> 01:28:55,290
What on earth happened?

2664
01:28:55,390 --> 01:28:56,840
[I'm not filming anymore]

2665
01:28:57,530 --> 01:29:00,270
[High-Speed to Ulsan coming soon]

2666
01:28:57,850 --> 01:29:00,560
Is this what a Manito is like?

2667
01:29:00,490 --> 01:29:01,660
[Ulsan Station — a new beginning in a new place]

2668
01:29:00,560 --> 01:29:04,200
Arrived in Ulsan,
the Secret Manito mission begins.

2669
01:29:01,810 --> 01:29:04,140
[Secret Manito]

2670
01:29:04,200 --> 01:29:05,310
A future rookie team.

2671
01:29:04,290 --> 01:29:06,510
[Future League — Ulsan Dolphins roster]

2672
01:29:05,310 --> 01:29:06,720
Ulsan Dolphins.

2673
01:29:06,720 --> 01:29:08,810
Having gone through dismissal,
I've experienced a lot of hardship.

2674
01:29:06,760 --> 01:29:08,650
[Their “second chapter of life” unfolds in Ulsan…
“Ulsan Dolphins” is formed]

2675
01:29:08,650 --> 01:29:09,600
[Korean baseball spreads its wings for change…]

2676
01:29:08,810 --> 01:29:10,550
But I'll keep fighting.

2677
01:29:09,600 --> 01:29:10,550
[The first citizen team “Ulsan Dolphins” is born
Image / Footage / Info: MBC]

2678
01:29:10,550 --> 01:29:13,320
We'll really need everyone's
support and encouragement.

2679
01:29:10,910 --> 01:29:13,430
[Meeting unexpected helpers!]

2680
01:29:13,540 --> 01:29:14,490
[Like behind-the-scenes footage…]

2681
01:29:14,540 --> 01:29:15,170
[We didn't film that]

2682
01:29:15,230 --> 01:29:16,080
Not for now, right?

2683
01:29:15,300 --> 01:29:18,680
[Proposing to form a Dolphin TV crew
and film bonus content for fans]

2684
01:29:16,080 --> 01:29:18,550
We can form a behind-the-scenes crew.

2685
01:29:18,550 --> 01:29:20,230
Fighting!

2686
01:29:18,830 --> 01:29:20,200
[Fighting — The Dolphin appearing too?]

2687
01:29:20,230 --> 01:29:22,150
Every 30 minutes, give me a short break.

2688
01:29:20,330 --> 01:29:23,040
[Dolphin Boyoung appears!
What kind of support will begin?]

2689
01:29:22,150 --> 01:29:23,200
Every 30 minutes.

2690
01:29:23,200 --> 01:29:24,820
Left, right, front, front.

2691
01:29:23,230 --> 01:29:26,260
[Continuously preparing without rest]

2692
01:29:24,820 --> 01:29:26,490
Dolphins, Dolphins—shout it out loud!

2693
01:29:26,490 --> 01:29:27,930
Ulsan Dolphins will never stop.

2694
01:29:26,780 --> 01:29:28,710
[(The support) won't stop]

2695
01:29:27,930 --> 01:29:28,930
-Power!
-OK!

2696
01:29:28,940 --> 01:29:30,040
[Fighting. Let's go, let's go!]

2697
01:29:29,950 --> 01:29:30,830
This is so nerve-wracking.

2698
01:29:30,250 --> 01:29:32,490
[Dolphin TV attempts
an undercover infiltration shoot!]

2699
01:29:30,830 --> 01:29:32,530
Keep your voices down.

2700
01:29:32,530 --> 01:29:34,680
We're here.

2701
01:29:32,640 --> 01:29:36,360
[Manito;
The Secret Manitos are training]

2702
01:29:34,680 --> 01:29:36,000
They're practicing.

2703
01:29:36,000 --> 01:29:38,180
-Fighting!
-Fighting!

2704
01:29:36,610 --> 01:29:37,890
[Seeing them in person, the excitement rises!]

2705
01:29:38,090 --> 01:29:38,900
[(Turns head)]

2706
01:29:39,100 --> 01:29:39,940
[Looks like they're coming over?]

2707
01:29:40,100 --> 01:29:41,420
[Real situation, real situation]

2708
01:29:41,670 --> 01:29:42,470
[(Push)]

2709
01:29:42,280 --> 01:29:43,730
Why bring them over here? Why?

2710
01:29:43,730 --> 01:29:46,060
Coach, why are you revealing it?

2711
01:29:43,810 --> 01:29:48,600
[A heart-stopping moment—shouts ring out]

2712
01:29:46,060 --> 01:29:48,080
Wait—darn it.

2713
01:29:48,620 --> 01:29:51,030
What are you filming? What show is this?

2714
01:29:48,740 --> 01:29:50,650
[The Manitos are in trouble?]

2715
01:29:50,810 --> 01:29:53,380
[Can they keep their identities
hidden until the end?]

2716
01:29:51,030 --> 01:29:52,100
Did you get my consent?

2717
01:29:52,100 --> 01:29:53,160
Did you get permission?
